parameters: ストーリー　物資護衛依頼 本番
I came on a request from the guild. Serena,
adventurer. \n< Serena >
What do you want, kid? \n< Man >
Has that bastard Guesclin finally let the fat get to
his brain? \n< Man >
I heard that you are a reliable and skilled
adventurer. \n< Man >
Shall we give it a try? \n< Serena >
Oh, that's right...yeah! \n< Man >
What? \n< Man >
My Affirbil is an impregnable armor. I feel no pain
or discomfort from a strike of that level. \n< Serena >
Hmm? \n< Man >
And my left-hand Secrecy is... \n< Serena >
お酒消去
Crush bone and flesh to powder with a single stroke. \n< Serena >
Hmph. you're not just a kid. \n< Man >
That's my charm. People who meet me let their guard
down first. Just like you. \n< Serena >
You've got some guts. Alright, it's not a bad idea
to have him as a guard. \n< Man >
I'm Ochre. Well, let's try to get along, okay? \n< Ochre >
Oh, I hope so. \n< Serena >

Faaa...I've been drinking too much lately... \n< Prostitute >
I love drinking, and I can't get by without it. Plus,
it's a good way to get people to like me. But I just
can't seem to avoid a terrible ending... \n< Prostitute >
If you're not sure what to do, just have a drink and
smile. It'll work out somehow. They're paying, and the
free booze is amazing. \n< Prostitute >
Even if something unpleasant happens, if you're drunk
the distraction makes it not so bad, you know. \n< Prostitute >
But if you get too drunk, it might affect your work
afterwards and you never know what could happen if you
pass out, so be careful. \n< Prostitute >
There are also people who come expecting that and are
willing to drink, and the store won't help unless it's
to a certain extent. \n< Prostitute >
...In the end, there's no choice but to protect
oneself. \n< Prostitute >
Oh my, a new friend, I see. How lovely...and how
pitiful. \n< Prostitute >
For you cute, this job is easy. The men who come to
places like this are blatant, and if you let them do
what they want, they'll pay you a cup of money. \n< Prostitute >
But that means allowing yourself to be used to please
others. If you choose to do that, you have to endure
and accept unpleasant things. \n< Prostitute >
And, patience is poison. It may be fine in small
amounts, but if you have too much, you'll feel sick
and won't be able to focus on your work. \n< Prostitute >
So if you really don't like it, you should have the
courage to reject it. The money you get will be less,
and the customers may hate you and leave you. \n< Prostitute >
But in the end, that's how you can work for a long
time. I guess the trick to the job is to take it easy
and steadily accumulate a variety of tasks, right? \n< Prostitute >
